    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "38a2c97a_3a7cc4df",
        "filename": "milo/frontend/appengine/templates/pages/builder.html",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 83,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-03-09T03:05:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "the fact that we have a full MiloBuild here and make a temp struct only to type shorter field names is a smell to me:\n- we do not really have encapsulation since we have the full milo build: one can still NOT write .BuildSummary. If CurrentBuilds was []*buildSummary, it would make more sense, but I understand that CurrentBuilds is public and buildSummary is not \n- i think it indicates a problem with MiloBuild itself. Imagine ui.MiloBuild is simpler, e.g. it has ExecutionTime, rather than Summary that has execution time. Would you still have buildSummary?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 83,
        "startChar": 15,
        "endLine": 83,
        "endChar": 27
      },
      "revId": "11f178f86f55cb1aed2c962724360b6ca3c84b4d",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "cc51ac42_b097f47e",
        "filename": "milo/frontend/appengine/templates/pages/builder.html",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 83,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002080
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-03-12T21:29:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The problem isn\u0027t shorter field names.  The problem is (for the lack of a better word) API boundaries between the view (templates) and the controller.  \nIt smells weird to have a struct with (for example) 50 fields in it, but only having the template use 10.  In that case I would argue that either the controller is doing excessive work, the view isn\u0027t showing enough, or theres a breakdown in abstraction.\n\nMaking ui.MiloBuild simpler wouldn\u0027t fix this, since there is still a struct being passed from the controller to the view with too many fields.\n\nI\u0027ll agree this smells way weird though.  I think making BuildSummary public, and the UI struct field to pass through makes more sense.",
      "parentUuid": "38a2c97a_3a7cc4df",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 83,
        "startChar": 15,
        "endLine": 83,
        "endChar": 27
      },
      "revId": "11f178f86f55cb1aed2c962724360b6ca3c84b4d",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
